parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall without warning, which can lead to accidents, especially at high speeds. This can also cause inconvenience and frustration to the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls intermittently and without warning at any speed
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the accelerator cable can cause the accelerator pedal to stick to the floor, leading to unintended acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The accelerator pedal sticks to the floor
the accelerator pedal does not return to its normal position
the accelerator pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.
